---
const faqs = [
  {
    q: 'What exactly is the Startup Incubator?',
    a: "A Valley Christian accelerator that mentors students building impactful businesses. This site covers one piece: registering your project in a shared list so it can be maintained and handed off. Your code stays in your own account.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Do I lose ownership of my code?',
    a: "No. Your project lives in your own account and stays yours — during the program and after you graduate. You only transfer it into the organization if you're leaving with no one lined up to take it over.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Which projects should be registered here?',
    a: 'Any incubator project worth keeping alive beyond your time on it — especially if you might graduate or switch focus.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Do I need to know Git and pull requests already?',
    a: "No. Learning the fork → edit → PR workflow is part of it. A mentor walks you through your first one.",
  },
  {
    q: 'What is the "tap" repository?',
    a: "One registry repo with a single JSON file listing every project. You register by opening a PR that appends an entry.",
  },
  {
    q: 'Who can pick up a registered project?',
    a: 'Any current Valley Christian student in the incubator. Browse the registry and talk to a mentor about taking one over.',
  },
  {
    q: 'What documentation does my project need?',
    a: "A README covering how to maintain, deploy, and learn the codebase. Clear hand-off docs are what make a project adoptable.",
  },
];
---

<section id="faq" class="relative mx-auto max-w-3xl scroll-mt-20 px-5 py-24 sm:px-8 md:py-32">
  <h2 class="reveal text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3.4rem)]">
    Frequently asked
  </h2>

  <div class="mt-10 space-y-3">
    {
      faqs.map((f, i) => (
        <details
          class="reveal group rounded-2xl border-[1.5px] border-ink bg-surface transition-[box-shadow] open:shadow-hard"
          data-reveal-delay={0.03 * i}
        >
          <summary
            class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-center justify-between gap-4 px-6 py-5 font-display text-lg font-bold"
          >
            {f.q}
            <span
              class="grid h-7 w-7 flex-none place-items-center rounded-full border-[1.5px] border-ink text-ink transition-transform duration-300 group-open:rotate-45 group-open:bg-saffron"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              +
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="-mt-1 px-6 pb-6 leading-relaxed text-ink-muted">{f.a}</div>
        </details>
      ))
    }
  </div>
</section>
